---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="7-Letter Words with X — Bingo Territory! Top Scoring X Words (2026)" description="Complete guide to 7-letter X words for Scrabble bingos. COMPLEX (20pts), TAXICAB (18pts), CONTEXT (16pts), EXPLOIT (16pts) and 40+ more ranked by score." keywords="7 letter words with x, scrabble x bingo words, seven letter x words, complex scrabble, taxicab scrabble, high scoring x bingos, x words bingo list">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"7-Letter Words with X — Bingo Territory! Top Scoring X Words","description":"Complete guide to 7-letter X words for Scrabble bingos. COMPLEX (20pts), TAXICAB (18pts), CONTEXT (16pts), EXPLOIT (16pts) and more.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/7-letter-words-with-x"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best 7-letter X words for Scrabble bingos?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"COMPLEX (20pts), TAXICAB (18pts), CONTEXT (16pts), and EXPLOIT (16pts) are top choices. With the 50-point bingo bonus, COMPLEX scores 70 points in a single turn before premium squares."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is X worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"X is worth 8 points in Scrabble, making it the third-highest tile after Q and Z (both 10 points). A 7-letter X bingo combines this high tile value with the 50-point bonus for using all rack tiles."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Should I hold X for a bingo or play it early?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"If you have X plus 5-6 common tiles (E, T, I, N, S, R), hold for a bingo. X combines well with common prefixes (EX-) and suffixes (-ING, -ION). If your rack is uncooperative after 2 turns, dump X on a premium square for 16-24 points."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">7-Letter Words with X — Bingo Territory!</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">X is worth 8 points — the third-highest tile in the game. When you land a 7-letter X word, that's your base score plus a 50-point bingo bonus. COMPLEX alone becomes a 70-point play. Here's your complete guide to 7-letter X bingos.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COMPLEX base</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">+50</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bingo bonus</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X tile in bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 7-Letter X Bingos by Score</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">COMPLEX — 20 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Consisting of many parts. C(3)+O(1)+M(3)+P(3)+L(1)+E(1)+X(8).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TAXICAB — 18 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A taxi. T(1)+A(1)+X(8)+I(1)+C(3)+A(1)+B(3). Common word, big score.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">CONTEXT — 16 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Surrounding circumstances. Uses very common tiles alongside X.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">EXPLOIT — 16 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">To use or a heroic deed. E(1)+X(8)+P(3)+L(1)+O(1)+I(1)+T(1).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Playable 7-Letter X Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MIXTURE</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EXPLAIN</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EXAMINE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EXAMPLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EXTREME</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TEXTILE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">X Bingo Strategy: EX- and -TION Patterns</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">The EX- prefix:</span> EX- opens dozens of 7-letter bingos: EXAMINE, EXPLAIN, EXPLOIT, EXPIRES, EXPLORE, EXTENDS. Hold E+X together — they're a bingo stem.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">X in the middle:</span> Words like TAXICAB, MIXTURE, TEXTILE place X centrally. These are harder to spot on your rack but equally valid bingos.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">X at the end:</span> COMPLEX, CONTEXT end with X. The -EX and -IX endings combine with many common 5-letter beginnings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Only 1 X tile:</span> Unlike Z (2 tiles), there's only one X in the bag. If your opponent plays it, no X bingo is possible. Track tile usage carefully.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">X bingos are more achievable than Z bingos because <span class="text-white font-medium">X pairs naturally with common letters</span>. The EX- prefix alone connects to hundreds of words. Your typical X bingo scores 66-70 points (16-20 base + 50 bonus) — a reliable game-winner.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/6-letter-words-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">6-Letter Words with X — Top Scoring Scrabble Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/4-letter-words-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">4-Letter Words with X — Complete Scrabble Guide</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all 7-letter X words instantly — free solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
